cs.CC, cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CG

The paper deals with proving the computational hardness of classic Nintendo games, which involves analyzing the complexity of game mechanics and designing algorithms to solve them. This falls under the scope of computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the AI and data structures used in the games, which could fall under cs.AI and cs.DS respectively. Finally, the paper also involves analyzing the geometry and graphics of the games, which could fall under cs.CG.
